-- Australia's Combet Says Government Committed to 5% Cut in Carbon Emissions
-- B y   M a r i o n   R a e
-- 2010-10-13T20:51:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/australia-s-combet-says-government-committed-to-5-cut-in-carbon-emissions.html
Australia is committed to a 5
percent cut in carbon emissions by 2020 with a market mechanism
considered the most efficient option, Climate Change Minister
Greg Combet told Australian Broadcasting Corp. radio today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marion Rae in Canberra at 
